hma; includes patients under 19 years of age with asthma receiving chronic high dose oral corticosteroid therapy (20 mg or higher daily dose of prednisone)], cancer, chronic anemia [including sickle cell anemia], alcoholism, or HIV infection); immunocomp

romised persons (functional asplenia, anatomic asplenia, , solid organ transplant [NOT during this hospitalization], bone marrow transplant over 12 months ago, AIDS, long-term corticosteroid use (> 20 mg a day of prednisone or equivalent), chemotherap

y or radiation more than 2 weeks before this hospitalization); CSF leak; cochlear implant, or patients who meet any of the criteria but are uncertain about prior vaccine status. Exclusion criteria (Must meet one): Patient received PPSV23 (Pneum

ovax) less than 5 years ago; patient received PCV13 (Prevnar) in the past 8 weeks;  patient reports allergic, febrile or neurologic reaction to pneumococcal vaccine; patient declines to receive vaccine; patient received shingles vaccine (Zostav

ax) in the past 4 weeks; pregnant patients; patients that have had a bone marrow transplant in the past 12 months; patients currently receiving a scheduled course of chemotherapy or radiation, patients who received chemotherapy or radiation within the la
st 2 weeks, patients receiving a solid organ transplant during this hospitalization.
